# Val Ark - local configuration template
#
# Copy this to ".env" (which is git-ignored) and edit for your machine:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Nothing host-specific is ever committed; .env holds YOUR paths only.
# All values are optional — Val Ark autodetects sensible defaults if unset.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATA ROOT — the disk Val Ark fills and measures free space against.
# Models live at   $VAL_ARK_DATA/models   (reused if already present)
# Everything else  $VAL_ARK_DATA/val-ark/{tools,content,sources,assets,installers,state}
#
# If unset, Val Ark autodetects the largest writable mount (/mnt/*, /data, ...),
# falling back to the repo directory for single-disk / dev use.
# VAL_ARK_DATA=/mnt/storage-10tb
# VAL_ARK_DATA=/srv/val-ark
# VAL_ARK_DATA=$HOME/val-ark-data

# Extra autodetect candidates (colon-separated), tried before the built-ins.
# VAL_ARK_DATA_CANDIDATES=/mnt/bigdisk:/data2

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DISK RESERVE — never fill past this. Keeps the OS/disk healthy and leaves
# headroom for the "cut back for smaller valuable files" curation rule.
# Reserve = max(VALARK_RESERVE_PCT% of total, VALARK_RESERVE_MIN_GB).
# VALARK_RESERVE_PCT=2
# VALARK_RESERVE_MIN_GB=50

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FINE-GRAINED OVERRIDES (rarely needed) — point individual trees elsewhere.
# VALARK_MODELS_DIR=/mnt/disk-a/models
# VALARK_TOOLS_DIR=/mnt/disk-b/tools
# VALARK_CONTENT_DIR=/mnt/disk-c/content

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL — raise GitHub API rate limits for link checks / release lookups.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REMOTE FLEET for the verification loop (space-separated user@host or host).
# Leave empty to skip remote checks. mDNS .local names work.
# VALARK_FLEET="node-a.local node-b.local user@10.0.0.20"
